Package: hdbayes
Title: Bayesian Analysis of Generalized Linear Models with Historical Data
Version: 0.0.1
Authors@R: c(person("Ethan M.", "Alt", email = "ethanalt@live.unc.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"), 
                    comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-6112-9030")),
             person("Xinxin", "Chen", role = "aut"),
             person("Luiz M.", "Carvalho", role = "aut"),
             person("Joseph G.", "Ibrahim", role = "aut")
             )
Description: User-friendly functions for utilization of (multiple) historical data set(s) in generalized linear models
             (GLMs). Contains functions for sampling from the posterior distribution of a GLM using the power prior 
             by Ibrahim and Chen (2000) <doi:10.1214/ss/1009212673>, normalized power prior (NPP) by Duan et al. 
             (2006) <doi:10.1002/env.752>, normalized asymptotic power prior (NAPP) by Ibrahim et al. (2015)
             <doi:10.1002/sim.6728>, commensurate prior by Hobbs et al. (2011) <doi:10.1111/j.1541-0420.2011.01564.x>, 
             robust meta-analytic-predictive prior (RMAP) by Schmidli et al. (2014) <doi:10.1111/biom.12242>, latent 
             exchangeability prior (LEAP) by Alt et al. (2023) <arXiv:2303.05223>, and the Bayesian hierarchical model.
